1344:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     * Theory:
1345:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  Setting the pointers to zero makes the system believe there is no data to
1346:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  read and writing will resume at address 0 overwriting any data that may have
1347:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  remained in the RAM.
1348:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *
1349:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     * Side Effects:
1350:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  Data waiting in the transmit buffer is not sent; a byte that is currently
1351:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  transmitting finishes transmitting.
1352:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *
1353:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *******************************************************************************/
