1409:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     * Theory:
1410:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  SendBreak function initializes registers to send 13-bit break signal. It is
1411:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  important to return the registers configuration to normal for continue 8-bit
1412:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  operation.
1413:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  There are 3 variants for this API usage:
1414:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  1) SendBreak(3) - function will send the Break signal and take care on the
1415:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     configuration returning. Function will block CPU until transmission
ARM GAS  C:\Users\JENNEW~1\AppData\Local\Temp\cc32J6Q4.s 			page 49


1416:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     complete.
1417:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  2) User may want to use blocking time if UART configured to the low speed
1418:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     operation
1419:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     Example for this case:
1420:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     SendBreak(0);     - initialize Break signal transmission
1421:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *         Add your code here to use CPU time
1422:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     SendBreak(1);     - complete Break operation
1423:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  3) Same to 2) but user may want to initialize and use the interrupt to
1424:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     complete break operation.
1425:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     Example for this case:
1426:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     Initialize TX interrupt with "TX - On TX Complete" parameter
1427:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     SendBreak(0);     - initialize Break signal transmission
1428:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *         Add your code here to use CPU time
1429:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     When interrupt appear with UART_MOVI_TX_STS_COMPLETE status:
1430:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *     SendBreak(2);     - complete Break operation
1431:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *
1432:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     * Side Effects:
1433:Generated_Source\PSoC5/UART_MOVI.c ****     *  The UART_MOVI_SendBreak() function initializes registers to send a
